🧩 Problem: Two Sum II (Sorted Array)

Given a 1-indexed array of integers numbers that is sorted in non-decreasing order, find two numbers such that they add up to a specific target number.

Note: 1-indexed array means array start from index 1 and not 0

📥 Input
An integer array numbers sorted in non-decreasing order
An integer target

📤 Output
Return an array [index1, index2] (1-based indices)

Example 1:

Input: numbers = [2,7,11,15], target = 9
Output: [1,2]

Input: numbers = [2,3,4], target = 6
Output: [1,3]

Solution:
class Solution {
    fun twoSum(numbers: IntArray, target: Int): IntArray {
        var i = 0
        var j = numbers.size - 1
        while(i < j){
            val sum = numbers[i] + numbers[j]
            // if sum is greater than target -> decrease j
            if(sum > target){
                j--
            }
            // if sum is smaller than target increase i++
            else if (sum < target){
                i++
            }else{
                return intArrayOf(i+1,j+1)
            }
        }
        return intArrayOf()
    }
}
